Taraba State Governor, Darius Ishaku has sacked his Commissioner of Information and Re-orientation Danjuma Adamu and his commissioner of Commerce, Trade and Industries Yusuf Njeke Tanimu. Ishaku in a press statement signed by his chief press secretary,  Mr. Iliya Bekyu Akweh, said the governor also approved a minor Cabinet reshuffle. The statement explained that the Commissioner of Science and Technology, Alhaji Alhassan Hamman Gassol, would oversee the Ministry of Information and Reorientation while the Hon. Commissioner of Cooperative and Poverty Alleviation  Hon. Jethro Yakubu Zikenyu will now oversee the Ministry of Commerce, Trade, and Industries. Rep. Onuigbo Bags Climate Champion Award Peterside Berates Wike’s Alleged Displacement Of 100,000 Rivers… The statement noted that executive order takes immediate effect.